author: @hyperxbeat
text: A Python Wheel (.whl) is a way to download packages if a normal pip installer isn't working (like pip install cx_Freeze) I often use them for my 64-bit computer on the Unofficial Python Package Index as there is usually no alternative on 64-bit operating systems for Python on a lot of packages. To install one you simply Shift+Right Click in the directory of the file in File Manager, then say 'pip install wheel' then 'pip install [File Name]'.
